<br>
I would also suspect DoT's.  I have dueled people that DoT my pet a few times.  I'll back off the pet, then the pet will go for them again, back off, pet attacks, back off... etc.<br>
<br>
The /pet back off clears the hate list, then the DoT does damage and the pet aggro's again.  I know this works this way.  Perhaps one of the mobs the pet kept breaking mez on DoT'd the pet so the pet kept re-engaging the target.<br>
<br>
Test this easily if you want.  Meet a druid/ranger/shaman/necro in an Arena.  Make a pet, tell it to guard.  Have them DoT the pet, then keep backing off the pet and watch him re-engage every tick. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
