<br>
A.  Its not spell casting related.  Not that once a pet casts a spell and a mob is mezzed that it wont land it.  A pet which spell casts and then a mob is mezzed before it lands then when it lands breaks mezzim saying that the instances where I have seen pets break mezz there was no spells involved.  <br>
<br>
B.  This bug occurs with DC pets, charmed pets, mage pets, necro pets, shaman pets, etc, etc, etc.  This proves point A because shaman pets, and melee charmed pets dont cast spells but still break mezz at certain times<br>
<br>
C.  This occurs in ALL zones.  I have seen it in at least 5 different ones so far at least<br>
<br>
D.  This problem seems to be fixable if you back the pet off.  Once the chanter lands a clean mezz and the pet is off it, if you command the pet to attack it once mezzed it will not.  <br>
<br>
These are what I know from what I have seen in game. <br>
<br>
